1. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with logical formalisms such as monadic second order logic and weighted monadic second order logic. 
2. cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the recognition of word functions by weighted automata. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with the representation and manipulation of data structures such as graphs and words. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper discusses the expressive power of different formalisms in terms of their computational complexity. 
5. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with mathematical structures such as semirings and rings.
